race.description: Ladbrokes Future Stars Series Heat 3 Mdn Plate
race.comment: SILVER BULLET (5) resumed with an encouraging run at Mornington when finding the line strongly for second over 1200m. He put up a good number there and should relish getting to 1400m for the first time. Drawn well for Ben Allen, he can track the pace and have the last say. THINKYAHOT (6) made good improvement rising from 1100m to 1300m last start, covering ground from a wide draw there in what was a strongly run affair. He can land in a better spot here and go one better. LOTTA CITY (11) stuck on well at Mornington last time out, not handling the heavy two back. She should be right there again. BUTTERSCOTCH (7) is a mare by The Autumn Sun who debuts for the Moody & Coleman yard. She's jumped out well and has to be respected.
